# Go SOP

- `gofmt` / `goimports` before commit; match `staticcheck` / `golangci-lint` when configured.
- Explicit errors — no silent `_` unless documented; wrap with `%w` for context.
- `context.Context` on I/O, HTTP, and RPC; honor cancellation and deadlines.
- Small packages, clear names; avoid `util` / `common` catch-alls.
- Interfaces at consumer side when practical; keep APIs narrow.
- Concurrency: prefer errgroup/channels with clear ownership; detect races with `-race` in CI when available.
- HTTP handlers: validate input, map errors to status codes, no stack traces to clients.
- Tests: table-driven `_test.go`; `go test ./...` for acceptance when applicable.
- Modules via `go.mod`; deliberate version pins; secrets via env only.
